1
00:00:34,994 --> 00:00:36,132
[This drama is fictional
and bears no resemblance to reality]

2
00:00:36,132 --> 00:00:37,050
[Some scenes feature AI technology]

3
00:00:37,050 --> 00:00:38,142
[All child and animal scenes
followed strict safety guidelines]

4
00:00:39,624 --> 00:00:43,753
[2011]

5
00:00:43,753 --> 00:00:45,196
[Class Motto: Beat the Other Class]

6
00:00:55,585 --> 00:00:59,192
Three, two, one.

7
00:01:04,799 --> 00:01:06,668
The sun is still high in the sky.

8
00:01:06,668 --> 00:01:08,778
- Did you skip lunch?
- Come on, hurry up!

9
00:01:08,778 --> 00:01:10,751
Okay.

10
00:01:10,751 --> 00:01:12,126
Faster!

11
00:01:12,126 --> 00:01:13,768
What are you doing? Faster!

12
00:01:13,768 --> 00:01:15,268
Run faster!

13
00:01:15,268 --> 00:01:17,745
You, harder!

14
00:01:17,745 --> 00:01:19,629
Got it.

15
00:01:24,001 --> 00:01:26,170
<i>Back then,</i>

16
00:01:26,170 --> 00:01:28,930
<i>I lived in a dream every day.</i>

17
00:01:38,751 --> 00:01:40,351
Don't film me.

18
00:01:40,351 --> 00:01:42,168
Why not?

19
00:01:42,168 --> 00:01:44,029
You're pretty.

20
00:01:45,356 --> 00:01:47,626
<i>Back then,</i>

21
00:01:47,626 --> 00:01:50,410
<i>I lived dreaming of you every day.</i>

22
00:02:10,793 --> 00:02:12,042
Excuse me, sir.

23
00:02:12,042 --> 00:02:13,410
Would you like to drink anything?

24
00:02:13,410 --> 00:02:14,802
Cold ale, please.

25
00:02:14,802 --> 00:02:16,895
Just a moment, please.

26
00:02:30,001 --> 00:02:31,502
Ian, you ready?

27
00:02:31,502 --> 00:02:33,111
Ju Yi Jae, what's taking so long?

28
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:35,723
- Coming.
- I'm coming!

29
00:02:36,741 --> 00:02:41,626
<i>But if I'm not the adult I wanted to be,</i>

30
00:02:41,626 --> 00:02:44,256
<i>does that mean I've failed?</i>

31
00:02:49,989 --> 00:02:54,050
<i>If I'm finally living the life I wanted,</i>

32
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:56,768
<i>does that mean I've succeeded?</i>

33
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:04,168
The 83rd European International Film Awards!

34
00:03:04,168 --> 00:03:07,737
And the Golden Wave Award goes to...

35
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:12,443
After the Rising Wave Award,
this makes two wins.

36
00:03:12,443 --> 00:03:17,998
Director Ian Woo's "Wandering".
Congratulations!

37
00:03:19,116 --> 00:03:21,012
[Ian Woo, Wandering]

38
00:03:40,638 --> 00:03:42,461
Thank you.

39
00:03:44,668 --> 00:03:46,894
Thank you.

40
00:03:46,894 --> 00:03:48,820
Thank you.

41
00:03:50,690 --> 00:03:55,484
I'd like to express
my heartfelt gratitude to everyone here.

42
00:03:55,484 --> 00:03:58,447
Since this is my second time on stage tonight,

43
00:03:58,447 --> 00:04:02,542
I'll keep it brief
and share the rest in Korean.

44
00:04:03,754 --> 00:04:09,625
Someone gave a lost 18-year-old boy a dream.

45
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:14,338
I dedicate this award to her.

46
00:04:14,338 --> 00:04:19,209
Never stop dreaming, no matter where you are.

47
00:04:19,209 --> 00:04:20,626
Thank you.

48
00:04:20,626 --> 00:04:22,521
Thank you so much.

49
00:04:28,793 --> 00:04:32,598
Your debut feature film
won the Golden Wave Award for Best Picture.

50
00:04:32,598 --> 00:04:34,150
Congratulations.

51
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:37,877
People are already calling you
a genius director.

52
00:04:37,877 --> 00:04:39,238
I'm honored.

53
00:04:39,238 --> 00:04:41,713
The trophy feels heavy in my hands.

54
00:04:42,418 --> 00:04:43,825
And it's so shiny.

55
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:46,251
Does it symbolize your future?

56
00:04:46,251 --> 00:04:47,459
Really?

57
00:04:47,459 --> 00:04:49,915
I'll have to go to that place.

58
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:52,459
Where will you be going?

59
00:04:52,459 --> 00:04:55,453
I'm going for a drink.

60
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:06,895
[Episode 1]

61
00:05:13,094 --> 00:05:16,233
Oh, my back.

62
00:05:16,233 --> 00:05:19,593
Yi Jae, you're wiping out the clams.

63
00:05:19,593 --> 00:05:21,822
I should hire you.

64
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:23,574
What do you say?

65
00:05:23,574 --> 00:05:26,494
Oh, how much are you paying?

66
00:05:26,494 --> 00:05:29,288
I've been a reporter for eight years.

67
00:05:29,288 --> 00:05:31,165
I've dug for clams plenty of times.

68
00:05:31,165 --> 00:05:35,209
I came here ready
to dig up the whole sea today.

69
00:05:35,209 --> 00:05:38,165
Now, that won't do.

70
00:05:38,165 --> 00:05:40,293
The tide's coming in soon.

71
00:05:40,293 --> 00:05:43,209
We should head out.

72
00:05:43,209 --> 00:05:48,126
Time flies when I'm chatting with you.

73
00:05:48,126 --> 00:05:49,945
Are you from Jeolla?

74
00:05:49,945 --> 00:05:52,305
Gyeongsang.

75
00:05:52,305 --> 00:05:56,918
When you walk on the flats,
watch out for these holes.

76
00:05:56,918 --> 00:05:59,826
Is this puddle a hole?

77
00:05:59,826 --> 00:06:01,028
Yeah.

78
00:06:01,028 --> 00:06:04,126
If you fall in, you're done for.

79
00:06:04,126 --> 00:06:06,667
Isn't life kind of like that, too?

80
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:10,587
Once you're in too deep, there's no way out.

81
00:06:19,710 --> 00:06:21,048
You okay, Yi Jae?

82
00:06:21,048 --> 00:06:22,508
- You okay?
- Damn it!

83
00:06:22,508 --> 00:06:25,393
Well, this is a mess!

84
00:06:30,376 --> 00:06:33,485
<i>Life is like a hole.</i>

85
00:06:35,229 --> 00:06:38,209
<i>Every step was a struggle,</i>

86
00:06:38,209 --> 00:06:40,276
<i>and consistently,</i>

87
00:06:40,276 --> 00:06:43,036
<i>it ended in disaster.</i>

88
00:06:52,454 --> 00:06:53,497
Yeah, what?

89
00:06:53,497 --> 00:06:54,668
<i>Have you eaten?</i>

90
00:06:54,668 --> 00:06:57,044
Yeah. And you?

91
00:06:57,044 --> 00:06:58,843
<i>Yeah.</i>

92
00:07:01,334 --> 00:07:02,626
What?

93
00:07:02,626 --> 00:07:04,599
<i>So...</i>

94
00:07:04,599 --> 00:07:08,001
<i>The landlord is raising the rent again.</i>

95
00:07:08,001 --> 00:07:09,119
Geez.

96
00:07:09,119 --> 00:07:11,499
At this rate, we'll have to sell the shop.

97
00:07:11,499 --> 00:07:14,810
Got it. I'll figure out the money.

98
00:07:14,810 --> 00:07:16,479
<i>Sorry.</i>

99
00:07:16,479 --> 00:07:18,209
<i>You feeling okay?</i>

100
00:07:18,209 --> 00:07:19,459
<i>How's your leg?</i>

101
00:07:19,459 --> 00:07:20,858
Must be the rain.

102
00:07:20,858 --> 00:07:22,459
It's aching a bit.

103
00:07:22,459 --> 00:07:25,684
<i>You're better than the weather forecast.</i>

104
00:07:26,710 --> 00:07:27,781
Mom,

105
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:29,241
I just got home.

106
00:07:29,241 --> 00:07:30,284
I'll hang up now.

107
00:07:30,284 --> 00:07:32,286
<i>Okay, get some rest.</i>

108
00:07:32,286 --> 00:07:34,212
Okay.

109
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:50,499
Oh, man.

110
00:07:53,918 --> 00:07:56,901
I'm dying.

111
00:08:07,668 --> 00:08:11,082
Someone please do this for me.

112
00:08:13,584 --> 00:08:16,830
I'll wear them again someday.

113
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:20,963
I'll need them then.

114
00:08:20,963 --> 00:08:22,764
Oh, man.

115
00:08:22,764 --> 00:08:27,044
Nobody's going to live my life for me.

116
00:08:28,793 --> 00:08:31,126
I should step on this.

117
00:08:31,126 --> 00:08:32,979
Seriously...

118
00:08:33,959 --> 00:08:37,393
- Should I just toss it?
<i>- "Wandering" is the director's first feature,</i>

119
00:08:37,393 --> 00:08:38,964
<i>based on his own life,</i>

120
00:08:38,964 --> 00:08:43,804
<i>portraying the life of an outsider
wandering across the Pacific.</i>

121
00:08:43,804 --> 00:08:47,152
<i>Compared to a rudderless ship adrift at sea...</i>

122
00:08:47,152 --> 00:08:48,862
<i>it captures the character's inner turmoil</i>

123
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:52,184
<i>with stunning sensitivity,
earning wide acclaim.</i>

124
00:08:52,184 --> 00:08:55,577
<i>With this film, Director Ian Woo
won both the Rising Director Award</i>

125
00:08:55,577 --> 00:08:57,663
<i>- and the Best Picture Award.</i>
- What a flashy debut.

126
00:08:57,663 --> 00:09:00,244
<i>It's a miraculous achievement.</i>

127
00:09:00,244 --> 00:09:01,751
<i>Notably, Director Ian Woo</i>

128
00:09:01,751 --> 00:09:04,042
<i>- being revealed as Korean</i>
- Korean?

129
00:09:04,042 --> 00:09:07,719
<i>has sparked intense interest from local media.</i>

130
00:09:07,719 --> 00:09:10,175
<i>Including a romantic message to his first love,</i>

131
00:09:10,175 --> 00:09:12,220
<i>News 10 brings you the moment.</i>

132
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:14,710
<i>Let's take a look.</i>

133
00:09:14,710 --> 00:09:20,209
<i>Who's the "she" you mentioned
during your acceptance speech?</i>

134
00:09:20,209 --> 00:09:23,947
<i>My first love.</i>

135
00:09:31,459 --> 00:09:32,880
Let's not go there...

136
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:36,084
Director, Korea's watching too!
Say something to your first love!

137
00:09:36,084 --> 00:09:37,805
Look over here, please.

138
00:09:39,994 --> 00:09:42,418
<i>You watching?</i>

139
00:09:42,418 --> 00:09:44,877
I kept my promise.

140
00:09:44,877 --> 00:09:47,762
Now I'm coming to see you.

141
00:09:50,793 --> 00:09:52,699
Woo Soo Bin?

142
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:55,262
No way...

143
00:09:55,262 --> 00:09:57,306
Woo Soo Bin...

144
00:09:57,306 --> 00:09:59,399
How?

145
00:10:00,226 --> 00:10:01,985
Woo...

146
00:10:04,376 --> 00:10:06,440
Woo... Damn it...

147
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,959
Soo...

148
00:10:07,959 --> 00:10:09,522
Bin.

149
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:11,439
What?

150
00:10:11,439 --> 00:10:13,713
Nothing's coming up.

151
00:10:16,334 --> 00:10:17,785
Ian Woo.

152
00:10:17,785 --> 00:10:19,162
Right, it's Ian Woo.

153
00:10:19,162 --> 00:10:24,625
Director Ian Woo.

154
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:28,712
[Director Ian Woo's "Wandering"
Scoops Two Awards]

155
00:10:31,548 --> 00:10:33,376
[Director Ian Woo's Acceptance Speech:
Rising Director Award at Europa Film Festival]

156
00:10:33,376 --> 00:10:34,301
<i>First...</i>

157
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:37,971
<i>- I want to express...</i>
- What's that? What's he even saying?

158
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:40,432
What the hell is he going on about?

159
00:10:41,683 --> 00:10:43,367
Ugh, no subtitles? Subtitles?

160
00:10:43,367 --> 00:10:45,486
Subtitles!

161
00:10:46,251 --> 00:10:48,168
<i>I'm going for a drink.</i>

162
00:10:48,168 --> 00:10:51,084
I'm going for a drink.

163
00:10:51,084 --> 00:10:53,202
Yeah, right.

164
00:10:54,780 --> 00:10:56,501
So annoying!

165
00:10:56,501 --> 00:10:58,534
Just try coming to Korea!

166
00:10:58,534 --> 00:10:59,869
No, wait.

167
00:10:59,869 --> 00:11:01,703
If you come, I swear!

168
00:11:01,703 --> 00:11:03,042
No.

169
00:11:03,042 --> 00:11:05,506
If you come, I'll kick you!

170
00:11:18,595 --> 00:11:21,890
[Director Ian Woo Heading to Korea?]

171
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:27,563
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
we'll be arriving at Incheon Airport shortly.</i>

172
00:11:27,563 --> 00:11:32,200
<i>Please fasten your seatbelts
and return your seats...</i>

173
00:11:41,838 --> 00:11:44,455
<i>Jenny said you went to Korea.</i>

174
00:11:44,455 --> 00:11:46,778
<i>This isn't international, right?</i>

175
00:11:46,778 --> 00:11:48,125
The weather is nice in Seoul.

176
00:11:48,125 --> 00:11:49,835
<i>Hey, you!</i>

177
00:11:49,835 --> 00:11:51,579
<i>If you're at the airport, give me 30 minutes.</i>

178
00:11:51,579 --> 00:11:54,131
<i>I'll release a story saying you flew in today.</i>

179
00:11:54,131 --> 00:11:56,699
<i>- Don't you want to get swept up by fans?</i>
- Hi.

180
00:11:56,699 --> 00:11:57,719
I'll pass.

181
00:11:57,719 --> 00:11:59,793
<i>- Hey, don't hang up.</i>
- Thanks.

182
00:11:59,793 --> 00:12:01,501
<i>Don't hang...</i>

183
00:12:01,501 --> 00:12:03,566
<i>I've been a reporter for eight years.</i>

184
00:12:07,626 --> 00:12:11,948
I guess young folks find that show fun too.

185
00:12:13,025 --> 00:12:14,755
Oh, sorry. What was that?

186
00:12:14,755 --> 00:12:17,946
I enjoy that show myself.

187
00:12:17,946 --> 00:12:19,655
Sorry. Carry on.

188
00:12:19,655 --> 00:12:22,159
I'm a fan of Ju Yi Jae.

189
00:12:22,159 --> 00:12:23,243
Is that right?

190
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:25,376
That reporter.

191
00:12:25,376 --> 00:12:30,084
That young lady masters every regional dialect.

192
00:12:30,084 --> 00:12:32,974
She's a hard worker, has a great appetite,

193
00:12:32,974 --> 00:12:38,545
and is incredibly polite to the elders.

194
00:12:38,545 --> 00:12:40,884
[Oops! Reporter Ju Yi Jae Takes a Tumble!]

195
00:12:40,884 --> 00:12:42,221
Sounds like she hasn't changed.

196
00:12:42,221 --> 00:12:45,432
Since you're headed to a hotel,

197
00:12:45,432 --> 00:12:48,810
I guess you don't live in Korea.

198
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:53,031
It's been a long time since I've been to Korea.

199
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:55,609
It's changed a lot.

200
00:12:55,609 --> 00:12:57,730
Oh, yeah.

201
00:12:58,543 --> 00:13:03,916
This country changes in the blink of an eye.

202
00:13:06,745 --> 00:13:10,590
[Get up, Ju Yi Jae!]

203
00:13:16,964 --> 00:13:19,424
<i>Are you the producer now?</i>

204
00:13:19,424 --> 00:13:21,760
Fine, then you be the producer.

205
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:26,223
The producer and writer spent a whole month
setting up and shooting at that grape farm.

206
00:13:26,223 --> 00:13:29,101
You think they're staying quiet
because they're fine with it?

207
00:13:29,101 --> 00:13:31,144
We were just on a boat two weeks ago.

208
00:13:31,144 --> 00:13:33,981
That was hairtail fishing,
this is gizzard shad fishing.

209
00:13:33,981 --> 00:13:34,985
Totally different.

210
00:13:34,985 --> 00:13:37,793
We're not getting any new shots.

211
00:13:37,793 --> 00:13:40,362
That's why I said pick one.

212
00:13:40,362 --> 00:13:42,324
New shots?

213
00:13:42,324 --> 00:13:46,417
Then maybe a different reporter
would give us new shots, huh?

214
00:13:49,329 --> 00:13:51,415
That threat doesn't work on me anymore.

215
00:13:51,415 --> 00:13:52,676
Threat?

216
00:13:52,676 --> 00:13:53,709
Oh, you really.

217
00:13:53,709 --> 00:13:56,209
- Hey, you.
- What, what?

218
00:13:56,209 --> 00:13:58,339
- Forget it. Let's just drop it.
- Talk.

219
00:13:58,339 --> 00:14:00,136
- CP, you're here?
- Hello.

220
00:14:00,136 --> 00:14:02,042
Hello.

221
00:14:02,042 --> 00:14:03,260
Hello.

222
00:14:03,260 --> 00:14:05,459
You're a total celebrity.

223
00:14:05,459 --> 00:14:06,626
Hello.

224
00:14:06,626 --> 00:14:07,835
- I'm a fan.
- Hello.

225
00:14:07,835 --> 00:14:09,517
- You're so cool.
- Listen up, everyone.

226
00:14:09,517 --> 00:14:11,936
- You're so handsome.
- You all know him, right?

227
00:14:11,936 --> 00:14:16,231
The hottest Director Ian Woo.

228
00:14:16,231 --> 00:14:17,626
Everyone, say hello.

229
00:14:17,626 --> 00:14:19,889
- You're good-looking.
- Hello.

230
00:14:19,889 --> 00:14:21,305
Thank you. Hello.

231
00:14:21,305 --> 00:14:22,835
Writer Song, where's Producer Kyung?

232
00:14:22,835 --> 00:14:24,478
Well...

233
00:14:25,574 --> 00:14:27,130
- Over there.
- Over there?

234
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:28,751
Knew it!

235
00:14:28,751 --> 00:14:31,290
No energy for life, but energy to drink?

236
00:14:31,290 --> 00:14:33,668
- What?
- And during lunch break?

237
00:14:33,668 --> 00:14:36,050
I can smell the baijiu and tangsuyuk on you.

238
00:14:36,050 --> 00:14:37,961
- I didn't.
- Large order of baijiu, right?

239
00:14:37,961 --> 00:14:39,070
Large order, my ass.

240
00:14:39,070 --> 00:14:41,629
I bet you got the large.
You always get the large.

241
00:14:41,629 --> 00:14:43,091
- Just a few hours ago.
- Shut up.

242
00:14:43,091 --> 00:14:44,092
- Why?
- Smile.

243
00:14:44,092 --> 00:14:46,186
- What?
- Act busy, quick!

244
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:56,835
Hey, Ju Yi Jae.

245
00:14:56,835 --> 00:14:57,948
What's wrong?

246
00:14:57,948 --> 00:15:00,835
<i>What? Why is he here?</i>

247
00:15:00,835 --> 00:15:02,903
Producer Kyung, let's talk.

248
00:15:02,903 --> 00:15:04,408
Sir.

249
00:15:04,408 --> 00:15:07,407
You should've just called me.
You came all the way here?

250
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:08,407
Oh, geez.

251
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:09,788
Yeah, hurry up.

252
00:15:09,788 --> 00:15:12,349
- What?
- The ratings are slipping.

253
00:15:12,349 --> 00:15:14,710
And I think I know why.

254
00:15:14,710 --> 00:15:18,843
Well... Is that a meeting or a fight?

255
00:15:23,251 --> 00:15:24,886
Hi.

256
00:15:25,668 --> 00:15:27,263
Huh?

257
00:15:54,168 --> 00:15:56,881
Hey, what took you so long?

258
00:16:17,710 --> 00:16:20,112
He looks good.

259
00:16:37,418 --> 00:16:39,042
What are you doing?

260
00:16:39,042 --> 00:16:40,650
Yeah.

261
00:16:42,416 --> 00:16:45,088
You are the future of Saero High,

262
00:16:45,088 --> 00:16:47,549
and the future of Korea.

263
00:16:47,549 --> 00:16:50,594
Aren't you our growing sprouts?

264
00:16:50,594 --> 00:16:54,585
To raise you into outstanding talent,

265
00:16:54,585 --> 00:16:57,559
every teacher here

266
00:16:57,559 --> 00:17:01,480
will give their full support,

267
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:04,191
so don't cause trouble

268
00:17:04,191 --> 00:17:06,651
and focus on your studies...

269
00:17:06,651 --> 00:17:07,775
Yi Jae!

270
00:17:07,775 --> 00:17:09,694
- Hey!
- Hey, you okay?

271
00:17:09,694 --> 00:17:11,095
- Hey, get up!
- I'll carry her.

272
00:17:11,095 --> 00:17:12,657
- Hey!
- You?

273
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:14,159
- You carry her.
- Careful.

274
00:17:14,159 --> 00:17:15,293
- Be careful.
- To the nurse's office!

275
00:17:15,293 --> 00:17:17,412
Move, move!

276
00:17:17,412 --> 00:17:19,190
Move!

277
00:17:27,918 --> 00:17:30,224
<i>Smells good.</i>

278
00:17:35,774 --> 00:17:36,915
Wait here.

279
00:17:36,915 --> 00:17:38,461
Yes.

280
00:17:43,209 --> 00:17:45,168
Is she gone?

281
00:17:45,168 --> 00:17:47,415
- You okay?
- Don't be dramatic.

282
00:17:47,415 --> 00:17:49,014
I was faking it.

283
00:17:49,014 --> 00:17:51,989
- Huh?
- But who are you?

284
00:17:51,989 --> 00:17:53,658
Mi Hyun was supposed to carry me.

285
00:17:53,658 --> 00:17:57,494
I just transferred. I'm in the next class.

286
00:17:57,494 --> 00:17:58,795
Oh, you're that guy.

287
00:17:58,795 --> 00:18:00,634
Seoul boy.

288
00:18:00,634 --> 00:18:02,423
Woo Soo Bin.

289
00:18:03,166 --> 00:18:05,426
You know me, don't you?

290
00:18:07,380 --> 00:18:09,131
<i>Hi.</i>

291
00:18:09,131 --> 00:18:12,425
Did I overreact?

292
00:18:12,425 --> 00:18:14,636
Anyway, assembly's over, right?

293
00:18:14,636 --> 00:18:16,459
Because you fainted,

294
00:18:16,459 --> 00:18:18,877
no more outdoor assemblies for a while.

295
00:18:18,877 --> 00:18:20,692
You all have me to thank.

296
00:18:20,692 --> 00:18:22,252
Growing sprouts, my ass.

297
00:18:22,252 --> 00:18:24,895
Sprouts will all fry in this sun.

298
00:18:24,895 --> 00:18:25,982
Right?

299
00:18:25,982 --> 00:18:31,243
Still, I was so worried watching you wobble.

300
00:18:34,209 --> 00:18:35,949
Were...

301
00:18:35,949 --> 00:18:37,751
Were you watching me?

302
00:18:37,751 --> 00:18:39,494
No.

303
00:18:39,494 --> 00:18:42,664
You just looked tired.

304
00:18:42,664 --> 00:18:44,918
Then we're even.

305
00:18:44,918 --> 00:18:46,751
Maybe I should act.

306
00:18:46,751 --> 00:18:48,514
Where are you going?

307
00:18:48,514 --> 00:18:50,211
Skipping class.

308
00:18:53,668 --> 00:18:55,136
Soo Bin,

309
00:18:55,136 --> 00:18:57,094
what's your dream?

310
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:58,584
Dream?

311
00:18:59,585 --> 00:19:01,474
I don't have one.

312
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:02,874
You don't have one?

313
00:19:02,874 --> 00:19:07,689
Hey, dude. A guy should have at least
one dream in his heart, right?

314
00:19:07,689 --> 00:19:09,448
I guess?

315
00:19:11,422 --> 00:19:14,626
But there's something I have to be.

316
00:19:14,626 --> 00:19:15,942
What?

317
00:19:15,942 --> 00:19:17,542
Doctor.

318
00:19:17,542 --> 00:19:21,036
My grandfather and father are both doctors.

319
00:19:21,036 --> 00:19:24,368
We moved here because of my dad's hospital.

320
00:19:24,368 --> 00:19:26,875
Are your grades good?

321
00:19:26,875 --> 00:19:28,102
No.

322
00:19:28,102 --> 00:19:29,822
They're excellent.

323
00:19:29,822 --> 00:19:31,334
Yeah?

324
00:19:31,334 --> 00:19:33,590
Sounds rough.

325
00:19:33,590 --> 00:19:35,216
Thanks.

326
00:19:36,259 --> 00:19:39,181
Now you ask about my dream.

327
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:44,976
What's your dream, Yi Jae?

328
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:48,814
This is why Seoul boys are trouble.

329
00:19:48,814 --> 00:19:51,282
Too smooth for no reason.

330
00:19:52,455 --> 00:19:55,744
Want a tip?

331
00:19:56,655 --> 00:19:59,335
Don't drop the last name
when you call someone here.

332
00:19:59,335 --> 00:20:00,856
They might get the wrong idea.

333
00:20:00,856 --> 00:20:02,877
- Be careful.
- Okay.

334
00:20:02,877 --> 00:20:05,295
Okay, Yi Jae.

335
00:20:05,295 --> 00:20:07,815
I told you not to.

336
00:20:07,815 --> 00:20:10,222
And don't smile like that.

337
00:20:10,855 --> 00:20:12,573
So...

338
00:20:12,573 --> 00:20:14,652
What's your dream?

339
00:20:16,387 --> 00:20:19,137
I want to be a film director!

340
00:20:19,137 --> 00:20:20,178
What do you think?

341
00:20:20,178 --> 00:20:21,980
Pretty cool, right?

342
00:20:35,235 --> 00:20:36,746
[Woo General Hospital]

343
00:20:45,704 --> 00:20:51,300
[Care with Heart. Strive for Excellence.
Inspire Happy Homes]

344
00:21:03,418 --> 00:21:05,738
Click, click, click.

345
00:21:07,543 --> 00:21:10,861
Okay, 30 minutes till sunset.

346
00:22:23,459 --> 00:22:24,952
Huh?

347
00:22:30,334 --> 00:22:31,807
You scared me.

348
00:22:31,807 --> 00:22:33,187
Hi.

349
00:22:33,187 --> 00:22:35,635
What are you doing here?

350
00:22:36,267 --> 00:22:37,941
I was running an errand for my dad.

351
00:22:37,941 --> 00:22:40,066
[Woo General Hospital]

352
00:22:40,066 --> 00:22:41,751
This is your dad's hospital?

353
00:22:41,751 --> 00:22:43,336
Yeah.

354
00:22:44,626 --> 00:22:46,247
Why are you here?

355
00:22:46,247 --> 00:22:48,611
To shoot the sunset.

356
00:22:53,075 --> 00:22:54,616
The patrol's coming soon.

357
00:22:54,616 --> 00:22:56,209
I should get going.

358
00:22:56,209 --> 00:22:58,215
You know the patrol schedule?

359
00:22:58,215 --> 00:22:59,751
This is a great spot for night shots.

360
00:22:59,751 --> 00:23:01,589
I'm out.

361
00:23:01,589 --> 00:23:02,715
Wait up.

362
00:23:02,715 --> 00:23:04,975
[Woo General Hospital]

363
00:23:10,751 --> 00:23:12,877
But...

364
00:23:12,877 --> 00:23:15,476
- why are we hiding...
- Be quiet.

365
00:23:35,875 --> 00:23:38,211
Who's there?

366
00:23:38,211 --> 00:23:40,074
Who's there?

367
00:23:40,074 --> 00:23:41,835
- Run!
- Huh?

368
00:23:41,835 --> 00:23:43,334
Stop!

369
00:23:43,334 --> 00:23:45,237
I said stop!

370
00:23:47,802 --> 00:23:50,046
[Woo General Hospital]

371
00:24:36,334 --> 00:24:38,569
I'm exhausted.

372
00:24:47,459 --> 00:24:49,084
From now on,

373
00:24:49,084 --> 00:24:51,168
we're accomplices.

374
00:24:51,168 --> 00:24:53,083
Okay?

375
00:24:56,001 --> 00:24:57,519
Yeah.

376
00:25:13,168 --> 00:25:14,815
Let's go.

377
00:25:41,585 --> 00:25:43,722
I'll get off here.

378
00:25:43,722 --> 00:25:45,126
Here?

379
00:25:45,126 --> 00:25:47,638
I just want to walk a bit.

380
00:25:48,742 --> 00:25:50,718
Don't be late for class, and call me.

381
00:25:50,718 --> 00:25:52,116
Love you, son.

382
00:25:52,116 --> 00:25:53,936
Yeah, Mom.

383
00:26:02,918 --> 00:26:05,136
That's great, ma'am.

384
00:26:05,136 --> 00:26:08,401
Your face tells a story.

385
00:26:08,401 --> 00:26:10,309
So lonely.

386
00:26:10,309 --> 00:26:12,126
Great look,

387
00:26:12,126 --> 00:26:14,373
amazing light.

388
00:26:15,201 --> 00:26:17,751
Something's missing.

389
00:26:19,012 --> 00:26:20,491
Shadow.

390
00:26:20,491 --> 00:26:22,464
You scared me.

391
00:26:25,209 --> 00:26:28,965
What if there were some shadow on her face?

392
00:26:28,965 --> 00:26:31,557
It'd look even lonelier.

393
00:26:41,710 --> 00:26:43,902
A little harder.

394
00:26:47,182 --> 00:26:49,984
No, what is this, a typhoon?

395
00:26:49,984 --> 00:26:52,744
Natural, keep it natural.

396
00:26:56,866 --> 00:26:57,742
[Mom]

397
00:26:57,742 --> 00:27:00,077
Soo Bin, focus.

398
00:27:00,077 --> 00:27:02,254
Yeah, sorry.

399
00:27:05,459 --> 00:27:07,462
Okay, that's perfect.

400
00:27:07,462 --> 00:27:09,344
Hold it.

401
00:27:12,162 --> 00:27:15,142
Who the hell are you? So loud.

402
00:27:15,142 --> 00:27:17,523
I can't sleep.

403
00:27:17,523 --> 00:27:19,730
Get the hell out.

404
00:27:21,168 --> 00:27:23,309
- That's my spot!
- Ma'am!

405
00:27:23,309 --> 00:27:25,123
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?

406
00:27:25,123 --> 00:27:26,964
Hey, you need to apologize!

407
00:27:26,964 --> 00:27:30,543
This little brat, glaring at me?

408
00:27:30,543 --> 00:27:31,764
Do you know who I am?

409
00:27:31,764 --> 00:27:33,126
- Forget it! Let's just go!
- Huh?

410
00:27:33,126 --> 00:27:35,071
- It's fine.
- The cops will know.

411
00:27:35,071 --> 00:27:37,083
I got it all on camera!

412
00:27:37,083 --> 00:27:39,166
See you at the police station.

413
00:27:39,877 --> 00:27:42,878
Give it back!

414
00:27:44,501 --> 00:27:47,139
Now what?

415
00:27:47,139 --> 00:27:48,293
Hand it over.

416
00:27:48,293 --> 00:27:49,293
Let go.

417
00:27:49,293 --> 00:27:50,835
- Hand it over!
- Damn it.

418
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:52,965
You little shit, you.

419
00:27:52,965 --> 00:27:55,390
Do you know who I am?

420
00:27:58,418 --> 00:28:00,293
Give me the camera.

421
00:28:00,293 --> 00:28:01,973
You little shit!

422
00:28:01,973 --> 00:28:03,182
Stop it!

423
00:28:03,182 --> 00:28:04,480
I said stop!

424
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:06,521
What?

425
00:28:06,521 --> 00:28:09,084
What the...

426
00:28:09,084 --> 00:28:11,126
I'll kill you, you shit.

427
00:28:11,126 --> 00:28:12,376
Get me that camera.

428
00:28:12,376 --> 00:28:14,001
Over there!

429
00:28:14,001 --> 00:28:15,585
That guy is beating him up!

430
00:28:15,585 --> 00:28:17,989
Drunk in broad daylight, beating on a kid?

431
00:28:17,989 --> 00:28:20,459
- Come here.
- Still haven't learned?

432
00:28:20,459 --> 00:28:23,084
You okay, kid?

433
00:28:23,084 --> 00:28:25,751
You miserable shit, this is becoming a habit!

434
00:28:25,751 --> 00:28:27,839
Where the hell did he go?

435
00:28:41,415 --> 00:28:43,442
You're tough. Really tough.

436
00:28:43,442 --> 00:28:46,503
Getting beaten up like that
and not making a sound.

437
00:28:47,459 --> 00:28:48,987
Sorry.

438
00:28:49,682 --> 00:28:50,822
It's fine.

439
00:28:50,822 --> 00:28:53,702
If it weren't for you,
that thing would've been ruined.

440
00:28:53,702 --> 00:28:55,126
But...

441
00:28:55,126 --> 00:28:57,307
it's still broken. That hurts.

442
00:29:08,751 --> 00:29:10,365
I...

443
00:29:11,042 --> 00:29:13,218
I'm going to like you.

444
00:29:16,168 --> 00:29:18,267
Is that okay with you?

445
00:29:21,209 --> 00:29:24,432
Not "I like you" but "I'm going to like you?"
What's that?

446
00:29:24,432 --> 00:29:25,723
I want to be like you.

447
00:29:25,723 --> 00:29:29,632
"I want to be like you?"
What's that supposed to mean?

448
00:29:29,632 --> 00:29:32,032
I've got pretty much everything.

449
00:29:32,032 --> 00:29:35,612
But there's one thing I don't have.

450
00:29:35,612 --> 00:29:37,528
Don't tell me...

451
00:29:37,528 --> 00:29:38,956
Me?

452
00:29:41,907 --> 00:29:43,322
A dream.

453
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:49,116
You have one.

454
00:29:50,209 --> 00:29:54,009
That's what makes you shine.

455
00:29:56,379 --> 00:29:58,918
<i>Those words...</i>

456
00:29:58,918 --> 00:30:02,553
<i>to someone like me
who had nothing but a dream...</i>

457
00:30:02,553 --> 00:30:05,062
<i>were like a spell.</i>

458
00:30:07,974 --> 00:30:10,317
<i>It was my first love.</i>

459
00:30:28,538 --> 00:30:31,630
<i>Let's make a movie together.</i>

460
00:30:35,083 --> 00:30:36,689
<i>Just imagine it.</i>

461
00:30:36,689 --> 00:30:40,668
<i>Our names side by side in the credits.</i>

462
00:30:40,668 --> 00:30:44,184
<i>We'll do something great together.</i>

463
00:30:58,650 --> 00:31:00,251
<i>But that spell...</i>

464
00:31:00,251 --> 00:31:03,275
<i>soon turned into a curse.</i>

465
00:31:15,084 --> 00:31:16,504
Are you out of your mind?

466
00:31:16,504 --> 00:31:18,085
What the hell are you doing here?

467
00:31:18,085 --> 00:31:19,604
Isn't this a TV station?

468
00:31:19,604 --> 00:31:21,005
Why else would I come to a TV station?

469
00:31:21,005 --> 00:31:22,334
Is this a coincidence?

470
00:31:22,334 --> 00:31:24,145
- A coincidence?
- Want me to say it's not?

471
00:31:24,145 --> 00:31:25,364
Hey!

472
00:31:25,364 --> 00:31:26,944
I was hoping I might see you.

473
00:31:26,944 --> 00:31:29,463
And seeing you... it's good.

474
00:31:29,463 --> 00:31:32,459
I missed you, Ju Yi Jae.

475
00:31:32,459 --> 00:31:35,652
- Did you not miss me?
- Bullshit.

476
00:31:36,297 --> 00:31:37,710
Still got that filthy mouth.

477
00:31:37,710 --> 00:31:39,565
Ain't nothing but rough memories...

478
00:31:39,565 --> 00:31:41,950
so I'm not sugarcoating it.

479
00:31:44,668 --> 00:31:45,918
What?

480
00:31:45,918 --> 00:31:47,956
What's going on?

481
00:31:49,877 --> 00:31:52,043
Anyone in there?

482
00:31:52,793 --> 00:31:55,714
- Get out of my face.
- You sure about that?

483
00:31:56,418 --> 00:31:58,278
It's not opening.

484
00:32:00,877 --> 00:32:02,209
Excuse me?

485
00:32:02,209 --> 00:32:03,591
It's not opening.

486
00:32:03,591 --> 00:32:05,084
Let's just take the elevator.

487
00:32:05,084 --> 00:32:06,892
Yeah, let's go.

488
00:32:10,585 --> 00:32:12,439
Move your hand.

489
00:32:13,079 --> 00:32:14,296
You got a boyfriend?

490
00:32:14,296 --> 00:32:15,835
Got a husband and a kid too.

491
00:32:15,835 --> 00:32:16,976
What about it?

492
00:32:16,976 --> 00:32:18,189
So you don't.

493
00:32:18,189 --> 00:32:20,906
Got time, then?

494
00:32:22,376 --> 00:32:24,543
Oops.

495
00:32:24,543 --> 00:32:26,156
You said let go.

496
00:32:26,156 --> 00:32:28,205
Sorry. Let's grab lunch.

497
00:32:28,205 --> 00:32:30,826
We're not exactly on lunch terms.

498
00:32:30,826 --> 00:32:34,794
- Side by side, then?
- I'm full. Had gukbap.

499
00:32:36,042 --> 00:32:39,418
Still funny as ever.

500
00:32:39,418 --> 00:32:41,669
Are you on some show or what?

501
00:32:41,669 --> 00:32:44,168
Going on about first love
and keeping promises...

502
00:32:44,168 --> 00:32:45,714
say any of that, and you're done.

503
00:32:45,714 --> 00:32:48,342
Korea's a small country.

504
00:32:48,342 --> 00:32:50,385
If I get doxxed, you taking the blame?

505
00:32:50,385 --> 00:32:52,644
So you've been keeping tabs on me.

506
00:32:52,644 --> 00:32:56,126
- I like that.
- Why are you stuck on that?

507
00:32:56,126 --> 00:32:57,270
Did you hate me a lot?

508
00:32:57,270 --> 00:32:59,337
Yeah, cursed you every day.

509
00:32:59,337 --> 00:33:01,710
But I guess the universe isn't on my side.

510
00:33:01,710 --> 00:33:04,275
Seeing you become a director and all,

511
00:33:04,275 --> 00:33:06,701
I could die of jealousy.

512
00:33:08,918 --> 00:33:10,700
You promised.

513
00:33:10,700 --> 00:33:12,637
To become a director.

514
00:33:12,637 --> 00:33:16,044
That promise broke
when you left for the States.

515
00:33:19,668 --> 00:33:20,916
Anyway.

516
00:33:20,916 --> 00:33:23,377
Pull that "hey" stunt again
and something else breaks.

517
00:33:23,377 --> 00:33:25,129
Best if we don't run into each other.

518
00:33:25,129 --> 00:33:27,555
Just steer clear, okay?

519
00:33:28,626 --> 00:33:29,657
Geez.

520
00:33:29,657 --> 00:33:31,476
What?

521
00:33:34,042 --> 00:33:35,635
You know?

522
00:33:37,084 --> 00:33:39,936
You lost a lot of brain cells today.

523
00:33:39,936 --> 00:33:41,937
Go home and pat yourself on the back.

524
00:33:41,937 --> 00:33:43,237
What are you on about?

525
00:33:43,237 --> 00:33:44,376
Are you nuts?

526
00:33:44,376 --> 00:33:46,007
Move.

527
00:33:49,376 --> 00:33:51,947
Knew it.

528
00:33:51,947 --> 00:33:52,948
[Stairwell]

529
00:33:52,948 --> 00:33:55,078
Already gone?

530
00:34:06,501 --> 00:34:08,847
Come on.

531
00:34:10,084 --> 00:34:11,459
Chicken's here!

532
00:34:11,459 --> 00:34:13,560
Hey, set the table.

533
00:34:15,221 --> 00:34:17,480
Thanks.

534
00:34:30,084 --> 00:34:32,376
Why do you always eat chicken at my place?

535
00:34:32,376 --> 00:34:34,114
You think I'm buying because you're cute?

536
00:34:34,114 --> 00:34:36,569
It's the curse of living alone, jerk.

537
00:34:36,569 --> 00:34:37,749
Cheers.

538
00:34:37,749 --> 00:34:39,298
Cheers.

539
00:34:46,626 --> 00:34:48,553
So good.

540
00:34:50,877 --> 00:34:52,506
Hey.

541
00:34:52,506 --> 00:34:54,848
Who hand-delivers profiles these days?

542
00:34:54,848 --> 00:34:56,547
Just use an agency.

543
00:34:56,547 --> 00:34:58,556
And quit the delivery gig.

544
00:34:58,556 --> 00:35:01,894
Every bike I see, I think of you.

545
00:35:01,894 --> 00:35:03,626
Your dad worries too.

546
00:35:03,626 --> 00:35:06,543
It's all about who you know.

547
00:35:06,543 --> 00:35:10,647
You never know when a familiar face
might catch a break.

548
00:35:10,647 --> 00:35:11,735
Plus,

549
00:35:11,735 --> 00:35:14,537
nothing beats delivery for flexible hours.

550
00:35:15,531 --> 00:35:16,782
Look at you, all grown up.

551
00:35:16,782 --> 00:35:19,660
If Young Jae were half like you,
I'd sleep like a baby.

552
00:35:19,660 --> 00:35:22,160
If I were your brother, I'd live just like him.

553
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:25,666
- Meaning what?
- You raised him that way.

554
00:35:25,666 --> 00:35:27,967
Can't argue with that.

555
00:35:30,334 --> 00:35:31,889
So?

556
00:35:32,631 --> 00:35:34,559
Finish what you were saying.

557
00:35:34,559 --> 00:35:36,001
Finish what? That's it.

558
00:35:36,001 --> 00:35:37,599
Huh?

559
00:35:37,599 --> 00:35:40,042
In front of your first love after a decade,

560
00:35:40,042 --> 00:35:42,251
hitting your head is the end?

561
00:35:42,251 --> 00:35:43,394
Right?

562
00:35:43,394 --> 00:35:46,334
Always me who gets broken.

563
00:35:46,334 --> 00:35:48,139
So how are you?

564
00:35:48,139 --> 00:35:51,168
- You okay?
- It's actually swollen. Feel it, right here.

565
00:35:51,168 --> 00:35:53,980
No, not your head. I mean how you're feeling.

566
00:35:53,980 --> 00:35:55,681
I mean, it was your dream.

567
00:35:55,681 --> 00:35:57,040
Being a director.

568
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:59,076
Are you okay with it?

569
00:35:59,076 --> 00:36:01,460
What, is dreaming first-come-first-served?

570
00:36:01,460 --> 00:36:03,795
Whoever's meant to make it, makes it.

571
00:36:05,001 --> 00:36:07,200
Your acting cool makes me sadder.

572
00:36:07,200 --> 00:36:10,000
- Honestly, if it weren't for Soo Bin's mom...
- Ian Woo.

573
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:12,129
- Huh?
- He's not Woo Soo Bin anymore.

574
00:36:12,129 --> 00:36:14,001
Don't call him that.

575
00:36:14,001 --> 00:36:16,050
What's the difference?

576
00:36:16,050 --> 00:36:17,635
Woo Soo Bin is the first love,

577
00:36:17,635 --> 00:36:19,793
and Ian Woo is the director?

578
00:36:19,793 --> 00:36:22,182
Does that make it easier?

579
00:36:22,182 --> 00:36:24,399
Yeah, it does.

580
00:36:25,161 --> 00:36:26,959
I've...

581
00:36:26,959 --> 00:36:29,106
I've imagined it hundreds of times.

582
00:36:29,106 --> 00:36:31,741
What it'd look like if we met again.

583
00:36:31,741 --> 00:36:33,567
But out of all those times,

584
00:36:33,567 --> 00:36:37,454
him being a director, me looking pathetic.
That wasn't one of them.

585
00:36:38,543 --> 00:36:40,361
I know I'm not okay.

586
00:36:40,361 --> 00:36:42,672
So just play along.

587
00:36:43,788 --> 00:36:46,188
How are you pathetic?

588
00:36:46,188 --> 00:36:48,116
You're amazing.

589
00:36:50,877 --> 00:36:54,456
Thinking I'm pathetic is
what makes me pathetic.

590
00:37:06,251 --> 00:37:09,730
<i>Daily Hollywood agreed to a written interview.</i>

591
00:37:09,730 --> 00:37:11,397
I saw the questions.

592
00:37:11,397 --> 00:37:12,815
I can skip what I don't want?

593
00:37:12,815 --> 00:37:15,234
<i>You always do.</i>

594
00:37:15,234 --> 00:37:19,459
I always have, but now my position's different.

595
00:37:19,459 --> 00:37:21,751
Don't want to seem arrogant.

596
00:37:21,751 --> 00:37:23,300
<i>I'll throw in a note.</i>

597
00:37:23,300 --> 00:37:25,780
<i>That you give consistently lazy answers.</i>

598
00:37:25,780 --> 00:37:27,621
That rumor needs to spread.

599
00:37:27,621 --> 00:37:30,899
You always polish them up, my answers.

600
00:37:30,899 --> 00:37:32,418
<i>For the rumor to spread,</i>

601
00:37:32,418 --> 00:37:35,720
<i>you'd have to get more famous.</i>

602
00:37:37,334 --> 00:37:39,591
Up for coming to Korea?

603
00:37:39,591 --> 00:37:42,010
- Working with a small-time director.
<i>- Nope.</i>

604
00:37:42,010 --> 00:37:44,638
<i>Big-shot producer's got it.</i>

605
00:37:44,638 --> 00:37:47,440
Heard Ian Woo's in Korea.

606
00:37:49,101 --> 00:37:50,427
Why is that even news?

607
00:37:50,427 --> 00:37:52,306
So annoying.

608
00:37:52,306 --> 00:37:53,814
- You're here.
- You're here.

609
00:37:53,814 --> 00:37:56,543
- Hi.
- Hi.

610
00:38:00,710 --> 00:38:02,706
Still, what a shame.

611
00:38:02,706 --> 00:38:05,625
I could've walked the red carpet.

612
00:38:06,366 --> 00:38:08,042
Queen of the Mediterranean.

613
00:38:08,042 --> 00:38:10,765
Oh Ha Na.

614
00:38:12,334 --> 00:38:14,668
Your first audition rejection ever.

615
00:38:14,668 --> 00:38:16,970
That was Ian's film, right?

616
00:38:18,168 --> 00:38:19,459
Chae Yeon.

617
00:38:19,459 --> 00:38:21,959
Who told you to be so brutally honest?

618
00:38:21,959 --> 00:38:24,798
Sorry. It's the braces...

619
00:38:27,376 --> 00:38:29,308
I just memorized my lines,

620
00:38:29,308 --> 00:38:31,174
why so many questions?

621
00:38:31,174 --> 00:38:33,001
Like some talk show.

622
00:38:33,001 --> 00:38:35,834
What did they ask?

623
00:38:35,834 --> 00:38:39,054
Didn't catch any of it. It was in English.

624
00:38:39,054 --> 00:38:41,855
Even though he speaks Korean,
he was all blah blah the whole time.

625
00:38:41,855 --> 00:38:44,054
So annoying.

626
00:38:44,054 --> 00:38:45,414
But, Ha Na.

627
00:38:45,414 --> 00:38:49,335
You said you didn't want
to do Hollywood films anyway.

628
00:38:49,335 --> 00:38:51,251
That CEO An made you,

629
00:38:51,251 --> 00:38:53,795
and you only auditioned because you had to.

630
00:38:53,795 --> 00:38:56,095
Anything Mom tells you to do,
you don't want to.

631
00:38:56,095 --> 00:38:57,418
And, Chae Yeon.

632
00:38:57,418 --> 00:39:01,894
I didn't want to. I failed.
Two different things.

633
00:39:01,894 --> 00:39:04,501
- Right?
- What does that mean?

634
00:39:04,501 --> 00:39:06,959
Let me touch you up.

635
00:39:06,959 --> 00:39:08,521
Sure.

636
00:39:12,001 --> 00:39:15,820
Whatever. Make her look pretty.

637
00:39:21,126 --> 00:39:22,476
Welcome.

638
00:39:22,476 --> 00:39:24,254
Hello.

639
00:39:25,418 --> 00:39:27,540
Ready to order?

640
00:39:29,334 --> 00:39:32,536
Iced Americano and a club sandwich.

641
00:39:32,536 --> 00:39:34,944
- Got it.
- Thanks.

642
00:39:35,835 --> 00:39:37,487
Woo Soo Bin?

643
00:39:49,692 --> 00:39:52,607
- Hey.
- Hey, Yu Geon.

644
00:39:56,418 --> 00:39:58,188
Long time.

645
00:39:58,188 --> 00:40:00,357
You got prettier.

646
00:40:00,357 --> 00:40:02,432
I've always been pretty.

647
00:40:02,432 --> 00:40:05,552
You became a director.

648
00:40:05,552 --> 00:40:08,352
Yeah, that happened.

649
00:40:08,352 --> 00:40:10,472
Can't say congrats, though.

650
00:40:10,472 --> 00:40:13,084
You lost the accent.

651
00:40:13,084 --> 00:40:15,334
You used to beg me for Seoul talk.

652
00:40:15,334 --> 00:40:16,878
Did I?

653
00:40:16,878 --> 00:40:18,859
Never followed you around.

654
00:40:18,859 --> 00:40:22,136
So I was just an excuse for Yi Jae?

655
00:40:22,835 --> 00:40:24,590
Get your facts straight.

656
00:40:24,590 --> 00:40:27,459
Yi Jae and I were tight first,
then you barged in.

657
00:40:27,459 --> 00:40:30,512
Made it three, and I got left out.

658
00:40:30,512 --> 00:40:32,681
You're still close with Yi Jae?

659
00:40:32,681 --> 00:40:36,020
Yeah. No reason not to be.

660
00:40:36,020 --> 00:40:39,273
The attitude's getting old.

661
00:40:39,273 --> 00:40:40,938
Didn't you use to like me?

662
00:40:40,938 --> 00:40:43,194
I'm on her side.

663
00:40:43,194 --> 00:40:45,376
If she doesn't like you,

664
00:40:45,376 --> 00:40:47,245
I don't either.

665
00:40:49,042 --> 00:40:52,291
That settles it. Have to settle this with her.

666
00:40:53,126 --> 00:40:54,543
Which reminds me,

667
00:40:54,543 --> 00:40:56,362
what's her number?

668
00:40:56,362 --> 00:40:59,613
I'll act as if I got it by chance,
so don't worry.

669
00:41:00,459 --> 00:41:02,127
You think I'd tell you?

670
00:41:02,127 --> 00:41:04,683
I know everything that went down.

671
00:41:04,683 --> 00:41:06,425
So what if you do?

672
00:41:06,425 --> 00:41:08,094
Stay out of it.

673
00:41:08,094 --> 00:41:10,177
Let the adults handle adult business.

674
00:41:10,177 --> 00:41:11,639
Well, then.

675
00:41:11,639 --> 00:41:14,102
Get the number yourself, grown-up.

676
00:41:14,102 --> 00:41:15,982
Anyway,

677
00:41:15,982 --> 00:41:18,437
it wasn't nice seeing you.

678
00:41:18,437 --> 00:41:21,271
Yeah, same here.

679
00:41:21,271 --> 00:41:22,273
Not yet?

680
00:41:22,273 --> 00:41:24,240
Just a moment.

681
00:41:29,907 --> 00:41:31,288
Hey, Yi Jae.

682
00:41:31,288 --> 00:41:32,407
What's up?

683
00:41:32,407 --> 00:41:33,453
This one's ready to go.

684
00:41:33,453 --> 00:41:36,376
Video tapes? Why are you selling them?

685
00:41:36,376 --> 00:41:40,168
What would I even do with them?
What are you talking about?

686
00:41:40,168 --> 00:41:43,009
Why sell tapes on Cabbage Market?

687
00:41:44,543 --> 00:41:46,804
Hey, why are you getting mad?

688
00:41:48,126 --> 00:41:50,224
Cabbage Market?

689
00:42:33,126 --> 00:42:34,983
So sorry.

690
00:42:34,983 --> 00:42:38,793
The model got into an accident on the way.

691
00:42:38,793 --> 00:42:41,793
We're urgently looking for a replacement,

692
00:42:41,793 --> 00:42:44,312
so please wait a little bit.

693
00:42:44,312 --> 00:42:46,223
Were they hurt badly?

694
00:42:46,223 --> 00:42:47,703
No.

695
00:42:47,703 --> 00:42:51,322
No visible injuries, but just in case.

696
00:42:52,042 --> 00:42:54,197
That's a relief.

697
00:42:54,197 --> 00:42:55,663
I'm fine waiting.

698
00:42:55,663 --> 00:42:58,037
No, you shouldn't be fine.

699
00:42:58,037 --> 00:43:01,459
The director is furious and rushing over.

700
00:43:01,459 --> 00:43:03,004
Why?

701
00:43:04,413 --> 00:43:06,626
You have a commercial shoot in two hours.

702
00:43:06,626 --> 00:43:09,303
We can't afford a delay.

703
00:43:12,342 --> 00:43:14,245
It's Brigitte Lin.

704
00:43:16,013 --> 00:43:17,959
Hey...

705
00:43:17,959 --> 00:43:19,619
Who are you?

706
00:43:21,269 --> 00:43:23,573
I'm waiting for the delivery payment.

707
00:43:23,573 --> 00:43:25,987
They went to get the corporate card.

708
00:43:27,376 --> 00:43:30,199
Wait here for a second.

709
00:43:33,418 --> 00:43:35,021
Oh Ha Na?

710
00:43:35,682 --> 00:43:36,784
Found him.

711
00:43:36,784 --> 00:43:38,950
Right there.

712
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:40,475
Pardon?

713
00:43:45,418 --> 00:43:47,228
Excuse me.

714
00:43:47,877 --> 00:43:49,264
Me?

715
00:43:49,264 --> 00:43:51,024
Do you have time?

716
00:43:51,024 --> 00:43:52,838
No, I don't.

717
00:43:58,668 --> 00:44:01,647
But you have a shoulder to lend me.

718
00:44:17,557 --> 00:44:19,527
It looks good on you.

719
00:44:26,251 --> 00:44:29,842
You're all set. Come over here.

720
00:44:41,835 --> 00:44:43,671
What's your name?

721
00:44:43,671 --> 00:44:45,186
I'm Sim Yu Geon.

722
00:44:45,186 --> 00:44:47,681
Are you in the business?

723
00:44:47,681 --> 00:44:50,176
How did you know?

724
00:44:50,176 --> 00:44:52,793
I act...

725
00:44:52,793 --> 00:44:55,061
I'm an aspiring actor.

726
00:44:56,459 --> 00:44:58,436
I see.

727
00:44:58,436 --> 00:45:00,956
I was actually asking about that.

728
00:45:04,459 --> 00:45:06,396
Well, it worked out anyway.

729
00:45:06,396 --> 00:45:08,916
I can tell you work out a lot.

730
00:45:08,916 --> 00:45:10,293
I have a good eye, right?

731
00:45:10,293 --> 00:45:12,843
I'm just naturally built.

732
00:45:15,333 --> 00:45:18,508
I can't believe this is happening to me.

733
00:45:18,508 --> 00:45:21,185
It's such an honor.

734
00:45:22,209 --> 00:45:24,459
It's no big deal.

735
00:45:24,459 --> 00:45:25,515
I should be thanking you.

736
00:45:25,515 --> 00:45:27,184
I'm a huge fan of Takeshi Kaneshiro.

737
00:45:27,184 --> 00:45:29,730
And now I'm playing him.

738
00:45:29,730 --> 00:45:31,235
Right?

739
00:45:32,918 --> 00:45:34,274
Not really.

740
00:45:34,274 --> 00:45:36,951
Just the shoulder guy?

741
00:45:37,818 --> 00:45:39,545
Shoulder guy...

742
00:45:39,545 --> 00:45:42,565
Alright, let's do a test shoot first.

743
00:45:42,565 --> 00:45:44,367
Just relax.

744
00:45:44,367 --> 00:45:48,645
Ha Na, could you lean on his shoulder?

745
00:45:48,645 --> 00:45:51,585
Yes, that's good.

746
00:45:51,585 --> 00:45:53,459
Good.

747
00:45:53,459 --> 00:45:54,835
Yes, perfect.

748
00:45:54,835 --> 00:45:56,543
Relax.

749
00:45:56,543 --> 00:45:58,072
Okay.

750
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:56,534
<i>Hold on.</i>

751
00:47:01,168 --> 00:47:03,370
<i>Take this.</i>

752
00:47:04,501 --> 00:47:06,074
<i>It won't be in the magazine.</i>

753
00:47:06,074 --> 00:47:08,125
<i>You're not disappointed, right?</i>

754
00:47:08,793 --> 00:47:09,995
<i>Thank you.</i>

755
00:47:09,995 --> 00:47:11,202
<i>I'm not signing it.</i>

756
00:47:11,202 --> 00:47:13,297
<i>Since you're not my fan.</i>

757
00:47:23,418 --> 00:47:25,579
It felt like a dream.

758
00:47:50,751 --> 00:47:54,380
They sell everything but cabbage.

759
00:47:58,960 --> 00:48:02,532
[Video Tapes]

760
00:48:04,632 --> 00:48:07,979
[Selling VHS tapes full of memories]

761
00:48:13,808 --> 00:48:16,150
[JuJu Video]

762
00:48:34,079 --> 00:48:37,245
[JuJu Video]

763
00:48:43,459 --> 00:48:45,444
My arm hurts.

764
00:48:47,251 --> 00:48:49,008
<i>Cabbage.</i>

765
00:48:50,512 --> 00:48:54,641
[Is this sold?]

766
00:48:54,641 --> 00:48:56,976
No, no.

767
00:48:56,976 --> 00:48:58,520
[No!]

768
00:48:58,520 --> 00:49:00,271
[Really? Why?]

769
00:49:00,271 --> 00:49:02,081
"Why?"

770
00:49:03,126 --> 00:49:05,743
What do you mean, why?

771
00:49:08,279 --> 00:49:12,992
[It's destiny. I'll buy them.]

772
00:49:12,992 --> 00:49:18,992
I'm selling them as a bundle. Is that okay?

773
00:49:20,542 --> 00:49:22,293
[Yes]

774
00:49:22,293 --> 00:49:24,303
Yes!

775
00:49:27,465 --> 00:49:29,084
[I only do in-person trades]

776
00:49:29,084 --> 00:49:30,750
Huh?

777
00:49:33,430 --> 00:49:38,093
[Under Construction]

778
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:47,944
Gosh, this is so heavy.

779
00:49:47,944 --> 00:49:50,537
Why did it have to be in person?

780
00:49:58,918 --> 00:50:02,917
<i>What the? Why is that jerk here?</i>

781
00:50:02,917 --> 00:50:05,928
<i>I just need to walk past him naturally.</i>

782
00:50:18,759 --> 00:50:21,318
LooksLikeAnEgg?

783
00:50:40,037 --> 00:50:41,080
I'm not selling them to you.

784
00:50:41,080 --> 00:50:42,254
- Double.
- No.

785
00:50:42,254 --> 00:50:43,291
- Triple.
- I said I'm not selling them.

786
00:50:43,291 --> 00:50:45,467
- Ten times.
- Ten times?

787
00:50:52,391 --> 00:50:54,712
Is flexing your money
at a secondhand market your hobby?

788
00:50:54,712 --> 00:50:57,092
I'll consider it. I was getting bored anyway.

789
00:50:57,092 --> 00:51:00,211
You've gotten worse at talking back.

790
00:51:00,211 --> 00:51:01,432
How did you hold it in back then?

791
00:51:01,432 --> 00:51:02,811
It was bearable.

792
00:51:02,811 --> 00:51:04,687
Not seeing you was harder.

793
00:51:04,687 --> 00:51:07,865
That's too bad.
Because looking at you is hard for me.

794
00:51:08,483 --> 00:51:09,552
Should I be fluttering?

795
00:51:09,552 --> 00:51:12,578
You're consistent in the weirdest way.

796
00:51:13,168 --> 00:51:15,247
Why are you throwing these away?

797
00:51:15,865 --> 00:51:17,432
- They're just baggage.
- Baggage?

798
00:51:17,432 --> 00:51:19,497
Why keep them when they just gather dust?

799
00:51:19,497 --> 00:51:21,628
I should sell them if I can.

800
00:51:23,491 --> 00:51:25,586
You cherished them. Won't you regret it?

801
00:51:25,586 --> 00:51:27,627
I should give you a high rating.

802
00:51:27,627 --> 00:51:30,304
You even comfort the seller.

803
00:51:32,543 --> 00:51:35,134
That's what you wrote.

804
00:51:35,134 --> 00:51:38,137
The video tapes that were with me

805
00:51:38,137 --> 00:51:41,396
during my most beautiful days.

806
00:51:41,396 --> 00:51:45,084
- These videos were my friends...
<i>- These videos were my friends,</i>

807
00:51:45,084 --> 00:51:49,566
<i>my teachers, and my dreams.</i>

808
00:51:49,566 --> 00:51:52,068
<i>These are 30 carefully selected masterpieces</i>

809
00:51:52,068 --> 00:51:55,293
<i>that are hard to find now.</i>

810
00:51:55,293 --> 00:51:59,376
<i>My mother ran a video rental shop,</i>

811
00:51:59,376 --> 00:52:01,835
<i>so there are stickers on them.</i>

812
00:52:01,835 --> 00:52:06,556
<i>I'll remove them if it bothers you.</i>

813
00:52:06,556 --> 00:52:08,543
<i>For personal reasons,</i>

814
00:52:08,543 --> 00:52:12,334
<i>they won't be with me for the rest of my life.</i>

815
00:52:12,334 --> 00:52:14,626
<i>But I hope they end up</i>

816
00:52:14,626 --> 00:52:17,817
<i>with someone better than me...</i>

817
00:52:17,817 --> 00:52:20,183
It was a heartbreaking farewell letter.

818
00:52:20,183 --> 00:52:22,314
It really touched my heart.

819
00:52:23,126 --> 00:52:25,226
Alright, let's hear your story.

820
00:52:25,226 --> 00:52:26,728
What are you going to do with these?

821
00:52:26,728 --> 00:52:28,695
Collecting memories.

822
00:52:29,656 --> 00:52:31,990
Might as well watch together, right?

823
00:52:32,859 --> 00:52:36,161
As you can see, I'm the one selling memories.

824
00:52:36,827 --> 00:52:38,997
Just give me the money.

825
00:52:50,504 --> 00:52:54,170
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

826
00:53:00,376 --> 00:53:02,168
With this,

827
00:53:02,168 --> 00:53:04,398
I'm thinking of making a movie.

828
00:53:09,601 --> 00:53:11,989
But it doesn't have an ending.

829
00:53:18,751 --> 00:53:20,998
Work on it with me.

830
00:53:24,952 --> 00:53:27,372
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

831
00:53:27,372 --> 00:53:30,183
[Written and Directed
by Ju Yi Jae & Woo Soo Bin]

832
00:53:39,706 --> 00:53:41,643
An ending?

833
00:53:54,001 --> 00:53:56,028
That took a while.

834
00:53:56,028 --> 00:53:57,742
Happy now?

835
00:54:14,711 --> 00:54:20,145
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

836
00:54:29,251 --> 00:54:31,459
<i>Woo Soo Bin!</i>

837
00:54:31,459 --> 00:54:33,572
<i>Woo Soo Bin!</i>

838
00:54:35,126 --> 00:54:36,752
Yi Jae!

839
00:54:37,599 --> 00:54:39,281
Ju Yi Jae!

840
00:54:44,641 --> 00:54:47,501
I hate being out in the rain.

841
00:54:49,334 --> 00:54:51,038
Do you?

842
00:54:54,001 --> 00:54:56,294
It was 15 days.

843
00:54:56,294 --> 00:54:58,292
At least 15 days.

844
00:55:00,334 --> 00:55:03,475
That's how long I waited at your door.

845
00:55:04,501 --> 00:55:10,103
Thinking, "The streetlights turned on
two minutes early today."

846
00:55:13,346 --> 00:55:15,986
But what did you do to me?

847
00:55:15,986 --> 00:55:18,031
How could you...

848
00:55:19,609 --> 00:55:22,740
Are you out of your mind?

849
00:55:23,404 --> 00:55:25,492
Do you not remember?

850
00:55:26,751 --> 00:55:28,659
- That's...
- You shouldn't have come back

851
00:55:28,659 --> 00:55:31,290
acting as if nothing had happened!

852
00:55:33,710 --> 00:55:36,717
You should've just remained my first love.

853
00:55:37,877 --> 00:55:40,073
Not my biggest regret.

854
00:55:51,793 --> 00:55:53,564
Woo Soo Bin.

855
00:55:54,293 --> 00:55:56,450
You are my regret.

856
00:55:58,209 --> 00:55:59,918
Go back to that day yourself.

857
00:55:59,918 --> 00:56:02,242
And see how I felt.

858
00:56:12,203 --> 00:56:14,012
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

859
00:56:30,793 --> 00:56:34,168
<i>My first love, who grew by feeding on my dream,</i>

860
00:56:34,168 --> 00:56:36,543
<i>Woo Soo Bin,</i>

861
00:56:36,543 --> 00:56:38,467
<i>has returned.</i>

862
00:57:59,147 --> 00:58:01,533
<i>It's a guest special today.</i>

863
00:58:01,533 --> 00:58:02,914
<i>Hello, Ju Yi Jae.</i>

864
00:58:02,914 --> 00:58:05,553
<i>- What exactly does your contract cover?
- I don't know.</i>

865
00:58:05,553 --> 00:58:07,668
<i>- Yi Jae.
- Are you crazy? The mic is on.</i>

866
00:58:07,668 --> 00:58:09,494
<i>Don't you know the director?</i>

867
00:58:09,494 --> 00:58:11,113
<i>No.</i>

868
00:58:11,113 --> 00:58:12,614
<i>Hello, here's my profile.</i>

869
00:58:12,614 --> 00:58:14,494
<i>That's why you're failing.</i>

870
00:58:14,494 --> 00:58:15,754
<i>I can tell just by looking.</i>

871
00:58:15,754 --> 00:58:17,414
<i>Whether someone will make it or not.</i>

872
00:58:17,414 --> 00:58:20,074
<i>I want to be a movie director too,
just like you.</i>

873
00:58:20,074 --> 00:58:22,334
<i>Let's do something great together.</i>

874
00:58:22,334 --> 00:58:25,413
<i>I guess Soo Bin is here to make it up to you.</i>

875
00:58:25,413 --> 00:58:28,809
<i>I'll return the dream I stole from you.</i>

876
00:58:28,809 --> 00:58:31,391
<i>Even your first love, if you want.</i>
